mWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Tuesday Epic Nights for January ~~</span><hr size=1> Ryland:  Hey, gratzos on the engagement!  This is the first I've heard of it.  /cheer<br>
<br>
On Epic looting:  unless an epic raid is organized for a specific purpose (e.g. get so-and-so their named-epic-drop) epic loot is distributed according to level and need (level first, then need).  This has been stated in the KoV loot rules thread (<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub55.ezboard.com/fknightsofvalor76584frm15.showMessage?topicID=4.topic)">pub55.ezboard.com/fknight...D=4.topic)</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> under paragraph E), parts 1 and 2.<br>
<br>
Several approaches were presented during Council discussions, as well as some additional discussion in the loot rules thread itself, but the Level-Need method received the majority approval.  Keep in mind that this does not necessarily mean it's the final decision; it's a work-in-progress such that the things that work will stay in place and those that don't will be revised.<br>
<br>
I think that no matter what method is chosen, one could argue a certain degree of bias in any of them so I encourage all to exercise patience and understanding during this time.  To help keep tensions to a minimum, I have but one request to everyone: if you have a criticism please try to offer a viable alternative approach, such as what Bascomb saying.  Of course, we can't try all of them at once so once again please be patient as we go through the alternatives until we find one that is most satisfactory and can be applied uniformly.<br>
<br>
Some commentary on Bascy's suggestion: you stated Honor System in the same breath as what amounts to a merit-based approach.  I don't see how Honor system looting would work here.  I'll use my Paw spires experience as a reference: one of the group member's starts looting corpses until either 3pp or a fine steel weapon is found; the same person loots multiple corpses if necessary until either of the conditions above is met.  Then the next person in alphabetical order follows the same procedure and the pattern repeats itself throughout the night.  No one checks for 3pp accuracy: it could be 5-50pp for all anyone really knows; it's up to the looter to be honest, hence the Honor System.  This system fails in the epic scenario since it becomes a point of contention as to who is the first to loot.<br>
<br>
We could continue discussions of the merits of the Merit-based (ya, sorry about the pun), Roll-the-dice, and other approaches but this gets off-topic for this thread.<br>
<br>
Important things to remember:<br>
1) We all come out ahead when we work together<br>
2) Trust is crucial to success<br>
