<br>
Again:<br>
<br>
Epic Loot will go to:<br>
<br>
1. Who need it the most &amp; level:<br>
This is based on how far along in your epic you actually are, if working on your epic at all. For example:<br>
<br>
Person A is level 49 he has his epic 1/2 done<br>
Person B is level 54 he has his epic 1/2 done<br>
<br>
Epic loot drops: it should go to B based on level.<br>
<br>
Again, the idea behind this is that level 49 will have his chance for his epic peice as well, as long as everyone participates in Epic Nights as an ongoing thing. Even if we do a zone &amp; get only one epic peice for one person each Tuesday, its an accomplishment &amp; it's one less person that needs an item.<br>
<br>
also what Badorin has pointed out:<br>
<br>
On Epic looting: unless an epic raid is organized for a specific purpose (e.g. get so-and-so their named-epic-drop) epic loot is distributed according to level and need (level first, then need). This has been stated in the KoV loot rules thread (pub55.ezboard.com/fknight...D=4.topic) under paragraph E), parts 1 and 2.<br>
<br>
So in the Case of myself, Faewynd &amp; Stormmy, I will get first jade reaver based on level, Fae the second then Stormmy.<br>
<br>
I would also like it noted that I have thought about how many people in the guild need epic peices from this zone. Druids, Rangers &amp; Shamans  That is why COM is held twice this month &amp; most likely will be that way in future months, until everyone gets what is needed.  By then we will be so sick of COM we will never want to go there again! =)  I sincerely hope this is the case.<br>
